<TITLE> Monir Ahmed appointed acting BFF chief </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 30 (bdnews24.com)Senior vice president Monir Ahmed was tasked with running the Bangladesh Football Federation after its president SA Sultan gave up his post for "personal reasons". The decision came from an emergency meeting held at the BFF House Sunday. "Senior vice president Monir Ahmed will now be acting as the BFF president as SA Sultan expressed his inability to continue as the president," BFF media manager Syed Ahmed Al Fatah told bdnews24.com after the meeting. On Dec 12, Sultan tendered his resignation to the FIFA president, but FIFA rejected Sultan's appeal and instructed the BFF to form the district and divisional football associations (DFAs) before the BFF election. The BFF extended the deadline for holding the FA elections of districts and divisionsnow to be completed by Jan 15 instead of Dec 30 and by Jan 25 respectively. The meeting also decided not to give the councillorship to those districts, which would not be able to complete the DFAs elections in line with revised schedules. bd
